section.def:
Category A officer (甲類人員) means an officer who is appointed to an established office and who is
            confirmed in an established office at the time of his retirement or resignation from the
            service;

paragraph.content:
in the case of an officer to whom paragraph (2)(a) applies, an
                    annual amount equal to 1/675 of his pensionable emoluments for each complete
                    period of 2 months of war service;

subsection.def:
non-effective pay (不再服務薪津) includes naval, military or air force pensions, retired pay or
                gratuities (other than war gratuities to which section 23 of the Finance
                (No. 2) Act 1945 (1945 c. 13 U.K.) applied);

relevant Government service (有關的政府服務期) means service under the Government or
                under the Government of the United Kingdom that may be taken into account in
                determining whether an officer is eligible by length of service for a pension;

subparagraph.content:
in respect of service before 1 April 1987, 1/80 of his highest
                        pensionable emoluments for each complete 3-year period of his pensionable
                        service;
